videos.description: SMU's Semi Ojeleye comes up with the block as the shot clock is winding down to force a Cincinnati turnover.
videos.headline: SMU forces shot clock violation with block

videos.description: SMU's  Semi Ojeleye drives to the basket and makes the layup after being fouled in a close game against Cincinnati.
videos.headline: SMU's Ojeleye makes tough and-1 layup

videos.description: Cincinnati's Kevin Johnson forces the turnover and throws down the dunk on the fastbreak.
videos.headline: Turnover leads to fastbreak dunk for Cincinnati

videos.description: Semi Ojeleye drains the 3-point bucket in transition to keep SMU within striking distance in the first half.
videos.headline: SMU's Ojeleye continues strong start with 3-pointer

videos.description: Shake Milton knocks down the 3-pointer for SMU as the two teams go back and forth in the first half.
videos.headline: SMU stays close with 3-pointer

videos.description: Jacob Evans makes his 5th 3-pointer of the game.
videos.headline: Cincinnati's Evans stays hot behind the line

videos.description: Kevin Johnson forces the turnover and then finishes the easy dunk on the other end for Cincinnati.
videos.headline: Cincinnati's Johnson throws down second fast-break dunk of game

videos.description: SMU's Shake Milton makes the corner 3-pointer to tie game against Cincinnati.
videos.headline: SMU's 3-point shooting keeps game close

videos.description: SMU'S Sterling Brown gets the offensive rebound to extend lead over Cincinnati.
videos.headline: SMU takes advantage of second chance opportunity

videos.description: Semi Ojeleye extends SMU's lead over Cincinnati to double digits with the layup.
videos.headline: SMU's Ojeleye makes tough and-1 layup

videos.description: SMU's Semi Ojeleye talks about how his team's strong defensive effort propelled them to the win over Cincinnati.
videos.headline: Breaking down SMU's hard fought win over Cincinnati

videos.description: No. 25 SMU gets 18 points from Semi Ojeleye and a double-double from Sterling Brown in a 60-51 win over No. 11 Cincinnati.
videos.headline: SMU hands Cincinnati first AAC loss
